First Read: 03-Feb-26
SB242 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to commercial driver licenses; to amend
5 Section 32-6-49.18, Code of Alabama 1975, to require certain
6 commercial driver license holders to possess a United States
7 work authorization to operate a commercial motor vehicle
8 within the state; to require an operator of a commercial motor
9 vehicle to have proficiency in the English language; to
10 provide for certain impoundment procedures; to create the
11 offense of presenting a false foreign commercial driver
12 license; to create the offense of operating a commercial motor
13 vehicle without proper documentation; and to provide for
14 penalties.
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
16 Section 1. Section 32-6-49.18, Code of Alabama 1975, is
17 amended to read as follows:
